group.name: Cooking Indian Food - exotic flavors from India.

description:
Having the right spices and ingredients in your kitchen will help you get started to try out the wonderful Indian recipes out there.

Once you have some of the very basic spices and ingredients needed to make Indian recipes then you can expand your horizons and fill your kitchen with other exotic Indian ingredients and have fun experimenting with the wonderful Indian cuisine.

Indian cuisine uses an extensive variety of herbs, spices and ingredients. Most recipes can be made with a basic group of ingredients.

You will learn what you will need to get started and what are the most common ingredients to have when cooking Indian food.

 

Getting Started Indian Cooking.
name: Getting Started with Indian Cuisine

description:
http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/e/7/a/event_137448762.jpegPav Bhaji is fast food dish which is one of the culinary delights from Mumbai, is like the cosmopolitan city of Mumbai(Bombay) itself.
A hurried meal for the man in the street. This is a spicy blend of vegetables in tomato gravy served with pav(bread) that is cooked with butter. This is truly an innovation that arose out of the necessity of providing a nice hot meal in a hurry and one that tickles the taste buds.

 

 

Pav in Marathi means a small loaf of bread. Bhaji in Marathi means vegetable dish. Pav bhaji consists of bhaji (a thick potato-based curry) garnished with coriander, chopped onion and a dash of lemon and baked pav.
name: Pav Bhaji  - bread and a potato based mixed vegetable curry

description:
Dal Tadka is a very common dish in the India, one standard mid day vegetarian meal.

It is a good source of high protein.

Tadka Daal served with plain boiled rice. If you prefer, you can add pretty much any side dish you like to enhance this already perfect combination.

Dal Tadka using three types of Indian lentils – tur dal (red gram), chana dal (Bengal gram) and moong dal (yellow dal).

 

Ingredient
name: Daal Tadka a preparation of pulses(dried lentils, peas or beans) With Rice

description: http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/b/c/0/event_142099392.jpegAloo Gobi is a traditional Punjabi main dish made out of potatoes, cauliflower and fine blend of spices or masalas. Main ingredients for preparing Aloo Gobi dish includes garlic, ginger, onion, coriander, tomato, and cumin. This punjabi special vegetarian cusine goes well with Paratha, Roti and Puris. It is very famous in north India and a popular Indian cusine worldwide. This recipe is also spelled as alu gobi or aloo gobhi or potato cauliflower curry.

description:
Classic tandoori chicken from India is marinated in yogurt, lemon juice, and plenty of spices, then grilled or broiled. Plan ahead. This recipe needs to marinate at least 8 hours or overnight

Tandoori Chicken is usually cooked in Hotels and Dhabas in a Tandoor oven, which are made of clay which heats upto 900 degrees F. This Tandoor oven creates a very special and unique flavour, which is attributed to the juices and fat that melt and fall from the Chicken into the hot burning charcoal, which imparts this delicious smoky flavour. As a Tandoor is not feasible in home, we could probably try it out in a Charcoal Barbecue.
name: Tandoori Chicken – the aromas and flavours are a delight to the senses!

description:
Malabar Prawns is a coconut milk based curry, but quite hot and spicy that is served with rice based dishes.

Malabari Cuisine is from the Southern Part of Konkan Coast, that is quite different from the Northern Konkan cuisine namely Malvani and Gonmantak. Usage of Tamarind and Curry leaves is the signature of Malabari Cuisine.
name: Malabar Prawn Curry - aromatic curry from the Kerala Region

description: Bhatura, also spelled as Batura or Bhatoora is a very famous deep fried puffed bread common in North India. It is usually served with Chole or Chickpeas Curry or with any Chicken curry. There are numerous recipes for chole and bhatura around the net… Some used to make Bhatura with yeast and some with baking powder… This is how I make Bhatura and Chickpeas Curry at home… and I followed this recipe all these years and it always comes out perfect….
name: Chole bhature - Deep Fried Indian Puffed Bread with Chickpeas Curry

description:
Most awaited....
Paneer Makhani or Butter Paneer is yet another well known north Indian classic. Cubes of succulent home made cheese are simmered in a creamy, tomato sauce. Anyone who is familiar with Indian cuisine, would not have missed this rich flavorful dish.
 Paneer is deep fried and cooked with curds, tomatoes & cooked with butter and Paneer (Indian cheese).
